SW wind 10 MPH. Slight chop. SW wind 10 MPH. Slight chop. 74 degrees. Mostly sunny. Took Secchi readings in three locations. East of Burn's in 45 feet - 17 feet 2 inches. South of Wavering/Shotwell's at approximately 35 feet - 17.75 feet and East of Kindschuh's - 18.5 feet.

More vegetation on north end than 2004. Two baby loons. Two mature eagles. Water calm with a slight chop. More vegetation on north end than 2004. Two baby loons. Two mature eagles. Water calm with a slight chop.
3 loons. Hazy. Muted fall color. Canada geese flying. Slight chop.
More aquatic plants. 1 baby red headed merganser.
1 loon hatched June 4- 2007. 2 mature eagles. Clear and sunny. Slight chop. More vegetation on north end.
vegetation building on north end. slight chop. clear and sunny.
Cloudy- slight chop. Aquatic plant beds proliferating especially on north end.
partly cloudy/mostly clear. moderate chop on the lake.
The weather was very overcast.  Prior to the testing there was little rain.  There was a  sighting of an immature loon during the testing.
The weather was very windy and partial clouds.  The lake was choppy and there was a fair amount of water-skier activity on the lake.
The weather was quite windy and cloudy.  The water was rough/choppy.
